Package com.gitblit

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IUserService
    Implementations of IUserService control all aspects of UserModel objects and user authentication.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AccessRestrictionFilter
    The AccessRestrictionFilter is an AuthenticationFilter that confirms that the requested repository can be accessed by the anonymous or named user.
    AddIndexedBranch
    Utility class to add an indexBranch setting to matching repositories.
    AuthenticationFilter
    The AuthenticationFilter is a servlet filter that preprocesses requests that match its url pattern definition in the web.xml file.
    AuthenticationFilter.AuthenticatedRequest
    Wraps a standard HttpServletRequest and overrides user principal methods.
    ConfigUserService
    ConfigUserService is Gitblit's default user service implementation since version 0.8.0.
    Constants
    Constant values used by Gitblit.
    DownloadZipFilter
    The DownloadZipFilter is an AccessRestrictionFilter which ensures that zip requests for view-restricted repositories have proper authentication credentials and are authorized.
    DownloadZipServlet
    Streams out a zip file from the specified repository for any tree path at any revision.
    EnforceAuthenticationFilter
    This filter enforces authentication via HTTP Basic Authentication, if the settings indicate so.
    FederationClient
    Command-line client to pull federated Gitblit repositories.
    FederationPullExecutor
    FederationPullExecutor pulls repository updates and, optionally, user accounts and server settings from registered Gitblit instances.
    FederationServlet
    Handles federation requests.
    FileSettings
    Dynamically loads and reloads a properties file by keeping track of the last modification date.
    FileUserService Deprecated
    GCExecutor
    The GC executor handles periodic garbage collection in repositories.
    GitBlit
    GitBlit is the servlet context listener singleton that acts as the core for the web ui and the servlets.
    GitBlitServer
    GitBlitServer is the embedded Jetty server for Gitblit GO.
    GitBlitServer.Params
    JCommander Parameters class for GitBlitServer.
    GitblitSslContextFactory
    Special SSL context factory that configures Gitblit GO and replaces the primary trustmanager with a GitblitTrustManager.
    GitblitTrustManager
    GitblitTrustManager is a wrapper trust manager that hot-reloads a local file CRL and enforces client certificate revocations.
    GitblitUserService
    This class wraps the default user service and is recommended as the starting point for custom user service implementations.
    GitFilter
    The GitFilter is an AccessRestrictionFilter which ensures that Git client requests for push, clone, or view restricted repositories are authenticated and authorized.
    IStoredSettings
    Base class for stored settings implementations.
    JsonServlet
    Servlet class for interpreting json requests.

    PagesFilter
    The PagesFilter is an AccessRestrictionFilter which ensures the gh-pages requests for a view-restricted repository are authenticated and authorized.
    PagesServlet
    Serves the content of a gh-pages branch.
    RedmineUserService

    you can login to gitblit with Redmine user id and api key.
    RobotsTxtServlet

    RpcFilter

    RpcServlet
    Handles remote procedure calls.
    SyndicationFilter
    The SyndicationFilter is an AuthenticationFilter which ensures that feed requests for projects or view-restricted repositories have proper authentication credentials and are authorized for the requested feed.
    SyndicationServlet
    SyndicationServlet generates RSS 2.0 feeds and feed links.
    WebXmlSettings
    Loads Gitblit settings from the context-parameter values of a web.xml file.

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    GitBlitException
    GitBlitException is a marginally useful class.
    GitBlitException.ForbiddenException
    Exception to indicate that the requested action can not be executed by the specified user.
    GitBlitException.NotAllowedException
    Exception to indicate that the requested action has been disabled on the Gitblit server.
    GitBlitException.UnauthorizedException
    Exception to indicate that the client should prompt for credentials because the requested action requires authentication.
    GitBlitException.UnknownRequestException
    Exception to indicate that the requested action can not be executed by the server because it does not recognize the request type.
